04/02/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- Over 1,000 health care workers at the Pristina University Clinic staged a protest Wednesday (February 3rd) outside the ministry of health. They are demanding better working conditions, regulation of health insurance and higher salaries. The protestors vowed to continue until conditions improve.
In other news, more than 500 police officers threatened to walk off their jobs Thursday if the government fails to fulfil a list of demands promised before local elections last November. The officers want a 100% salary increase and permanent contracts. Their current base salary is 215 euros a month. (Koha Ditore, Lajm, Express, Kosova Sot, Zeri - 04/02/10)
